      <description>Major General R.C.A. Edge lived in India with his parents and returned to
            England with his family in 1920 when he was eight years old. He returned to India as an
            adult and served in the British Army (Royal Engineers), the Bombay Sappers and Miners,
            and the Survey of India.</description>
